# ğŸš¨ Critical Error Prevention Guide for Adding News Articles

## TOP CRITICAL RULES - NEVER VIOLATE THESE:

### 1. ğŸš« NEVER REFERENCE NON-EXISTENT IMAGES
- **ERROR**: Referencing image files that don't physically exist in the assets folder
- **CONSEQUENCE**: Build failure, deployment failure
- **PREVENTION**: ALWAYS verify image files exist before adding references
- **CHECK**: Use file explorer to confirm `src/assets/images/news/[folder]/[image]` exists

### 2. ğŸš« NEVER CREATE MARKDOWN BEFORE IMAGES
- **ERROR**: Writing markdown file before uploading images to assets folder
- **CONSEQUENCE**: Broken image references, build failures
- **PREVENTION**: Upload all images FIRST, then create markdown
- **ORDER**: Images â†’ Verify existence â†’ Write markdown

### 3. ğŸš« NEVER SKIP BUILD VERIFICATION
- **ERROR**: Committing without running `npm run build` locally
- **CONSEQUENCE**: Production build failures
- **PREVENTION**: ALWAYS run `npm run build` and verify success before committing

## MANDATORY PRE-CREATION CHECKLIST:

### Phase 1: Image Preparation (CRITICAL)
- [ ] ğŸ¯ Create directory: `src/assets/images/news/YYYY-MM-DD-[title]/`
- [ ] ğŸ“ Upload ALL required images to this directory
- [ ] âœ… Verify files exist using file explorer (not just memory)
- [ ] ğŸ“· Ensure featured image exists (usually `image.jpg` or `featuredimage.jpg`)
- [ ] ğŸ” Check file names are exactly as they'll be referenced (case-sensitive)

### Phase 2: Markdown Creation
- [ ] ğŸ“ Create markdown file: `src/content/news/YYYY-MM-DD-[title].md`
- [ ] ğŸ·ï¸ Add complete frontmatter with ALL required fields
- [ ] ğŸ–¼ï¸ Set featuredImage path to EXISTING image file
- [ ] ğŸ–¼ï¸ Set SEOImage path to EXISTING image file (if different)
- [ ] ğŸ“¸ Only reference images that physically exist in content body

### Phase 3: Verification (MANDATORY)
- [ ] ğŸ”¨ Run `npm run build` locally
- [ ] âœ… Verify build completes without errors
