## COMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:

### A. Image Path Errors
âŒ **WRONG**: `featuredImage: "image.jpg"` (missing full path)
âœ… **CORRECT**: `featuredImage: "../../assets/images/news/2025-07-22-[title]/image.jpg"`

âŒ **WRONG**: Case mismatch: `Image.JPG` vs actual `image.jpg`
âœ… **CORRECT**: Exact case match with actual filename

âŒ **WRONG**: Assuming image exists without verification
âœ… **CORRECT**: Physically check file exists before referencing

### B. Directory Structure Errors
âŒ **WRONG**: Creating markdown in wrong location
âœ… **CORRECT**: Always use `src/content/news/` for news articles

âŒ **WRONG**: Using inconsistent folder naming
âœ… **CORRECT**: `YYYY-MM-DD-[descriptive-title]` format

### C. Build Process Errors
âŒ **WRONG**: Committing without local build test
âœ… **CORRECT**: Always run `npm run build` before commit

âŒ **WRONG**: Ignoring build error messages
âœ… **CORRECT**: Fix all errors before proceeding

